KAIZER Chiefs and John Paintsil have come to an agreement to terminate his contract as the assistant coach of the Club with effect from 6 June 2017. His contract was due to expire in June 2018.Both parties have signed a separation agreement, the terms of which are confidential.&nbsp;The Club thanks John for his contribution and wish him well for his future endeavors.&nbsp;The 35-year-old for Ghana international, was appointed as Steve Komphela&rsquo;s assistant coach at the beginning of the 2016/17 Absa Premiership campaign.&nbsp;Breaking News! Chiefs part ways with Paintsil: https://t.co/oyTTMV9WEE&mdash; Kaizer Chiefs (@KaizerChiefs) June 8, 2017